7001e2fa3cb5f6d856fba5c369cddc","isMergeCommit":false,"messageTitle":"Add assertions to enforce internal invariants in Event, Deadline and AddCommand","messageBody":"- Add assertion in Event constructor to ensure end datetime is not\n  before start datetime\n- Add assertion in Deadline constructor to ensure due datetime is\n  not null\n- Add assertion in AddCommand to ensure command input is not null\n- Document important assumptions about object state and inter-class\n  contracts\n\nThese assertions formalize key internal invariants that should\nalways hold if earlier validation logic is functioning correctly.\nAn Event must not have an end datetime earlier than its start\ndatetime, a Deadline must always have a valid due datetime, and\nAddCommand should never receive a null command input.\n\nThe assertions serve as defensive programming safeguards to detect\nprogrammer logic errors early during development. They do not\nreplace user input validation and do not affect normal production\nbehaviour when assertions are disabled.\n\nThis improves code clarity by making implicit assumptions explicit\nand strengthens internal correctness guarantees.\n","tags":["A-FullCommitMessage"],"fileTypesAndContributionMap":{"txt":{"insertions":2,"deletions":0},"java":{"insertions":7,"deletions":1}}},{"hash":"dc736bd5cff78a09c707a7b60b1e357d567f22f2","isMergeCommit":true,"messageTitle":"Merge pull request #2 from calijacked/branch-A-Assertions","messageBody":"Branch a assertions","fileTypesAndContributionMap":{}},{"hash":"e9f40a46822136e8f484c687337cec43356df1ff","isMergeCommit":false,"messageTitle":"Improve code quality for AddCommand class","messageBody":"","fileTypesAndContributionMap":{"txt":{"insertions":2,"deletions":0},"java":{"insertions":217,"deletions":68}}},{"hash":"6d77d969757f8dd8772c147dd5ee23db2696775b","isMergeCommit":false,"messageTitle":"Refactor Parser and add comprehensive JUnit tests for command validation","messageBody":"- Updated Parser class to improve code readability, maintainability, and input validation:\n  • Added Javadoc comments to the class and methods, explaining responsibilities and parameters.\n  • Consolidated command argument extraction logic with clear constants and naming.\n  • Enforced non-empty argument checks for commands that require descriptions:\n      - \u0027todo\u0027 must have a description.\n      - \u0027deadline\u0027 must include a description and \u0027/by\u0027 datetime.\n      - \u0027event\u0027 must include a description, \u0027/from\u0027 datetime, and \u0027/to\u0027 datetime.\n  • Retained semantic validation (date format, logical ordering of event dates) in AddCommand.\n  • Improved error messages for clarity to users.\n\n- Updated AddCommandTest JUnit class:\n  • Added tests for creating TODO, DEADLINE, and EVENT tasks successfully.\n  • Added tests for failure cases including:\n      - Invalid event datetime formats.\n      - Event \u0027to\u0027 datetime before \u0027from\u0027 datetime.\n      - Invalid deadline date.\n      - Missing \u0027/by\u0027, \u0027/from\u0027, or \u0027/to\u0027 tags.\n  • Ensures AddCommand enforces semantic rules without overlapping Parser responsibilities.\n\n- Updated ParserTest JUnit class:\n  • Added tests for empty or missing arguments for TODO, DEADLINE, and EVENT commands.\n  • Verified that invalid commands throw RagebaitException.\n  • Retained tests for mark, unmark, delete, list, and exit commands.\n  • Improves coverage of input validation at the parsing layer.\n\nThis commit ensures a clear separation of responsibilities:\n  - Parser: syntactic validation and creation of the appropriate Command object.\n  - AddCommand: semantic validation of task-specific rules.\nIt also improves code quality, readability, and robustness, while providing comprehensive test coverage for both expected successes and failure cases.\n","fileTypesAndContributionMap":{"txt":{"insertions":2,"deletions":1},"java":{"insertions":105,"deletions":58}}},{"hash":"93765